  "prompt": "What will be my rank if I have scored 132/200 in MU-OET?",
  "response": "Your rank in the MU-OET (Manipal University Online Entrance Test) depends on several factors, including the overall performance of all candidates who took the exam that year, the difficulty level of the exam, and the number of students who appeared for it. \n\nTo estimate your rank with a score of 132 out of 200, you would typically need to look at the previous year's score distribution and cut-off ranks. If you have access to that data or can find that information online, you might be able to get a clearer idea of where your score might place you.\n\nHigher scores generally correspond to higher ranks, but without specific data from the current year's results, it's impossible to provide an exact rank. For the most accurate information, I recommend checking with official MU-OET resources or contacting the admissions office of Manipal University.",
